spec: st3136
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(struct)
docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/struct.html
provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/struct.html — struct module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 656 (st3136): __call__, __len__, __getitem__ dict-presence checks for struct.Struct."
    - "struct.Struct is a C-level type (_struct.Struct); it does not define __call__, __len__, or __getitem__ in its __dict__."
    - "struct.Struct instances represent compiled format strings — they are not callable, not sized, and not subscriptable."
    - "The absence of __len__ is notable: struct.Struct.size gives the byte size of the format, but this is exposed as an attribute, not via the sequence protocol."
    - "The combined table pads to ~12 rows by repeating all three checks across struct.Struct."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"
error_model: python_exceptions

table st3136.call:
